WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:04.237
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.304 --> 00:05.772
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.839 --> 00:07.207
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.273 --> 00:08.608
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.675 --> 00:10.510
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.577 --> 00:13.980
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:14.047 --> 00:15.048
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.115 --> 00:16.483
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.549 --> 00:17.650
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:17.717 --> 00:19.386
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.452 --> 00:21.421
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.488 --> 00:22.922
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:22.989 --> 00:24.924
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.991 --> 00:28.061
<i>- ♪ Loud, Loud, Loud ♪</i>

00:28.128 --> 00:29.696
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.763 --> 00:30.697
{\an8}- Poo-poo.

00:35.668 --> 00:38.605
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:38.671 --> 00:44.577
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:44.644 --> 00:46.946
- Watch in awe
as the Amazing Lincoln

00:47.013 --> 00:49.883
displays his unbelievable
yo-yo skills.

00:49.949 --> 00:52.419
I shall now walk the dog.

00:52.485 --> 00:54.788
Not you, Charles.
I meant the yo-yo.

00:54.854 --> 00:56.523
- [whining]

00:56.589 --> 01:00.193
- I shall now go
around the world.

01:00.260 --> 01:02.762
Sorry, still talking
about the yo-yo.

01:02.829 --> 01:04.864
- [whining]

01:04.931 --> 01:06.032
[banging]

01:06.099 --> 01:08.501
[crashing]

01:08.568 --> 01:13.306
- The Amazing Lincoln will now
take a brief intermission.

01:13.373 --> 01:14.541
Yikes.

01:14.607 --> 01:16.409
I better go tell Lisa.

01:16.476 --> 01:20.747
- You've completely destroyed
my life's work!

01:20.814 --> 01:24.851
I despise you,
and you no longer exist to me!

01:24.918 --> 01:26.352
- Yeah, I'm not telling Lisa.

01:26.419 --> 01:27.787
- [whining]

01:27.854 --> 01:30.423
- Oh, come on, Charles,
when did you get a conscience?

01:30.490 --> 01:32.292
I've seen you poop
on the couch.

01:32.358 --> 01:34.561
Besides, if I just walk away,

01:34.627 --> 01:37.831
what's the worst thing
that could happen?

01:37.897 --> 01:42.969
I'll just remove the evidence,
and they'll be none the wiser.

01:43.036 --> 01:46.039
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:46.105 --> 01:47.440
[explosion]

01:48.608 --> 01:52.045
{\an1}- I don't understand
what went wrong.

01:52.111 --> 01:55.415
Science is a fickle mistress.

01:55.482 --> 01:56.716
{\an3}- Hi, Lori.

01:56.783 --> 01:59.452
{\an3}Have we always had a window
in our closet?

01:59.519 --> 02:01.421
{\an1}- [sighs]
It's not a window.

02:01.488 --> 02:04.090
{\an1}Lisa's experiment blew
a hole in the wall.

02:04.157 --> 02:06.025
What's this?

02:06.092 --> 02:08.228
"To my bodacious babe"?

02:08.294 --> 02:10.196
{\an1}Leni, why is this picture
of Bobby hidden

02:10.263 --> 02:11.231
on your side of the closet?

02:11.297 --> 02:12.599
- Oh, there it is.

02:12.665 --> 02:14.234
{\an3}That was a surprise present
from Bobby

02:14.300 --> 02:15.869
for your 88-day-a-versary.

02:15.935 --> 02:18.471
{\an3}He asked me to hide it for him,
but I forgot where I put it.

02:18.538 --> 02:21.274
- That anniversary
was eight days ago.

02:21.341 --> 02:23.276
And Bobby gave me socks.

02:23.343 --> 02:24.711
I can't believe this.

02:24.777 --> 02:27.113
{\an1}You're literally seeing Bobby
behind my back!

02:27.180 --> 02:28.815
You are no longer my sister!

02:28.882 --> 02:32.218
- Everything okay after that
unexpected and totally random

02:32.285 --> 02:34.387
explosion that I know
nothing about?

02:34.454 --> 02:36.623
- Argh!
[slamming door]

02:36.689 --> 02:38.791
[crashing]

02:40.927 --> 02:41.995
- What happened?

02:42.061 --> 02:43.663
- A shelf fell on your head.

02:43.730 --> 02:45.131
- Of course.

02:45.198 --> 02:47.534
Everyone knows that an object
falling at a velocity

02:47.600 --> 02:49.769
of 9.8 meters
per second squared

02:49.836 --> 02:52.705
will result in a temporary
loss of consciousness.

02:52.772 --> 02:53.940
- I knew that.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.975
{\an3}The question is,
how did you?

02:56.042 --> 02:57.810
- Hey, I saw this
in a movie once.

02:57.877 --> 03:00.513
{\an1}I bet getting hit on the head
altered Leni's brain

03:00.580 --> 03:01.915
and made her smart.

03:01.981 --> 03:04.784
{\an3}- Lincoln, you seem unable
to distinguish between

03:04.851 --> 03:08.021
{\an3}scientific fact and preposterous
Hollywood schlock.

03:08.087 --> 03:09.589
- I don't get it.

03:09.656 --> 03:10.590
{\an3}- See?

03:10.657 --> 03:11.891
Same old Leni--

03:11.958 --> 03:14.661
{\an3}can't even understand
simple English.

03:14.727 --> 03:16.596
- No, I don't get
why you multiplied

03:16.663 --> 03:19.699
your Z-polynomials
before solving your non-negative

03:19.766 --> 03:21.100
integer exponents.

03:22.735 --> 03:23.670
- [gasps]

03:23.736 --> 03:25.138
- Now, if you'll excuse me,

03:25.204 --> 03:27.674
I'm off to disprove
Newtonian physics.

03:27.740 --> 03:29.509
{\an3}Bye-bye!

03:29.576 --> 03:33.046
- My world no longer
makes sense.

03:33.112 --> 03:34.280
- [growling]

03:34.347 --> 03:36.182
{\an3}- Don't you have a couch
to poop on?

03:36.249 --> 03:38.718
Charles, that was
a rhetorical question.

03:38.785 --> 03:39.719
{\an3}- [whines]

03:39.786 --> 03:40.887
- [screaming]

03:40.954 --> 03:42.288
[smashing]

03:42.355 --> 03:43.690
[panting]
- What are you so upset about?

03:43.756 --> 03:45.959
{\an3}- I just got kicked off
all my sports teams

03:46.025 --> 03:47.393
because I'm failing school!

03:47.460 --> 03:49.896
{\an1}- How could you fail?
Doesn't Lisa tutor you?

03:49.963 --> 03:52.899
- She used to, until she
dropped out and got a job

03:52.966 --> 03:56.102
as a gas station attendant
at Flip's Food N' Fuel.

03:56.169 --> 03:57.103
- She what?

03:57.170 --> 03:58.438
{\an3}- Ugh!

03:58.504 --> 04:01.708
{\an3}Without sports,
my life is meaningless!

04:01.774 --> 04:06.512
- I present to you
your new Miss Cute, and--

04:06.579 --> 04:07.680
[smash]

04:07.747 --> 04:10.116
Ow, my nose!

04:10.183 --> 04:11.651
[gasps]

04:11.718 --> 04:14.087
I am a hideous monster.

04:14.153 --> 04:16.356
- It's not that bad, Lola.

04:16.422 --> 04:18.690
- My pageant career is over!

04:18.757 --> 04:22.762
[smashing, teeth crackling]
Oh, my teeth!

04:22.829 --> 04:24.864
{\an1}[sobbing]

04:24.931 --> 04:26.099
- [growling]

04:26.165 --> 04:30.236
- Fine.
I'll fix it.

04:30.303 --> 04:31.304
[tires screeching]

04:31.371 --> 04:33.473
{\an1}Lisa, why are
you doing this?

04:33.539 --> 04:34.807
{\an3}- Flip's the only guy
who'll hire

04:34.874 --> 04:37.343
{\an3}four-year-olds
with no experience.

04:37.410 --> 04:40.246
{\an1}- No, I mean, why are you
doing any of this?

04:40.313 --> 04:42.015
{\an1}Come home.
Lynn needs you.

04:42.081 --> 04:45.385
- Why don't you get
Miss Smarty-Pants to help her?

04:45.451 --> 04:46.853
Speak of the devil...

04:46.919 --> 04:49.522
Regular or unleaded?
- Oh, I don't need gas.

04:49.589 --> 04:52.225
{\an1}I just won the Nobel Prize
for inventing a car

04:52.291 --> 04:54.060
that runs on apple juice.

04:54.127 --> 04:55.728
- Of course you did.

04:55.795 --> 04:58.831
- Fill her up, please.

04:58.898 --> 05:01.167
- And then we'll all get
in Leni's juice-mobile,

05:01.234 --> 05:03.236
go home, and forget
all this nonsense.

05:03.302 --> 05:05.772
{\an1}- Can't, I'm off to Harvard.
<i>Au revoir!</i>

05:05.838 --> 05:09.342
{\an1}<i>Adios! Auf Wiedersehen.</i>
And <i> aloha.</i>

05:09.409 --> 05:12.879
- Aha!
<i>Aloha</i> means "hello."

05:12.945 --> 05:15.281
- It also means "good-bye."

05:15.348 --> 05:17.684
- Dang it,
I used to know that.

05:17.750 --> 05:21.587
{\an1}- Hey, Chatty Cathy,
back to work!

05:21.654 --> 05:22.889
[phone ringing]

05:22.955 --> 05:24.524
- Hello?
Charles?

05:24.590 --> 05:26.325
<i>- [barking]</i>
- She's what?

05:26.392 --> 05:28.795
<i>- [barking]</i>
- All right, I'm on my way.

05:28.861 --> 05:31.364
- Look who it is--
Miss Soon-to-Heal.

05:31.431 --> 05:32.732
- [grunting]

05:32.799 --> 05:33.866
What do you want?

05:33.933 --> 05:35.101
- [screaming]

05:35.168 --> 05:36.469
I mean, you're looking better.

05:36.536 --> 05:40.773
- Oh, nice try, Lincoln,
But I am out of here.

05:40.840 --> 05:43.910
I can't stay
where I'm constantly reminded

05:43.976 --> 05:45.578
of my former self--

05:45.645 --> 05:49.549
my beautiful, beautiful self.

05:49.615 --> 05:51.284
- But--but--

05:51.350 --> 05:52.618
- [grunting]

05:52.685 --> 05:53.419
{\an1}[smack!]

05:53.486 --> 05:57.123
I'll send for this.

05:57.190 --> 05:58.191
- Lola, wait!

05:58.257 --> 05:59.826
Oof!

05:59.892 --> 06:02.528
{\an3}<i>- Careful, Lincoln, you get</i>
<i>could seriously injured.</i>

06:02.595 --> 06:04.597
{\an1}- Lana, what are you
doing in there?

06:04.664 --> 06:06.499
- I saw what happened
to Lola.

06:06.566 --> 06:08.334
Life is a fragile thing.

06:08.401 --> 06:10.069
I don't want to take any risks.

06:10.136 --> 06:12.472
- But you're the queen of risks.

06:12.538 --> 06:14.540
{\an3}-<i> Was</i> the queen
of risks.

06:14.607 --> 06:18.411
{\an3}From now on, I'll stay
in here where it's safe.

06:18.478 --> 06:21.147
{\an3}You know what I'm talking about,
huh, Geo?

06:21.214 --> 06:23.015
- Lana, you can't be serious.

06:23.082 --> 06:24.417
Lana?

06:24.484 --> 06:26.686
<i>- ♪ Things have</i>
<i>gotten drastic ♪</i>

06:26.753 --> 06:29.055
<i>♪ Now my sister</i>
<i>lives in plastic ♪</i>

06:29.122 --> 06:32.892
<i>♪ Where did it all go wrong? ♪</i>

06:32.959 --> 06:34.894
- Luna?
- Check it, bro.

06:34.961 --> 06:37.296
I uploaded a song I wrote
about our family

06:37.363 --> 06:39.265
going down the highway to--
hello!

06:39.332 --> 06:42.001
I just got 50 more hits!

06:42.068 --> 06:43.236
[crashing]

06:43.302 --> 06:45.772
{\an1}- [gasps]
Mick Swagger?

06:45.838 --> 06:49.776
{\an3}- Your singing is amazing.
You got to join my tour!

06:49.842 --> 06:51.978
- Luna is in!

06:52.044 --> 06:55.915
{\an1}- Don't you leave too!
The family's falling apart!

06:55.982 --> 06:57.416
- Sorry, dude!

06:57.483 --> 06:59.218
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

06:59.285 --> 07:01.387
- Clyde, this is Lincoln.
Come in.

07:01.454 --> 07:02.622
I've got a code blue!

07:02.688 --> 07:03.923
- Code blue?

07:03.990 --> 07:05.491
{\an3}You did something wrong
and lied about it

07:05.558 --> 07:07.293
and now everything
is all messed up?

07:07.360 --> 07:08.995
{\an1}- Affirmative.
Can you come over?

07:09.061 --> 07:11.264
{\an3}- Negative.
I've got a code green.

07:11.330 --> 07:13.132
{\an1}- You showed up to school
in your underwear?

07:13.199 --> 07:15.201
- No, that's code orange.

07:15.268 --> 07:17.036
{\an3}Hang on.

07:17.103 --> 07:18.938
[camera shutter clicks]

07:19.005 --> 07:21.073
- Sweet mother of--

07:21.140 --> 07:22.742
{\an1}What are you doing
with Lori?

07:22.809 --> 07:24.744
{\an3}- I've been trying
to tell you.

07:24.811 --> 07:29.515
A code green: Lori broke up with
Bobby, and I'm the rebound guy!

07:29.582 --> 07:34.020
{\an1}- Happy eight-minute-a-versary,
shnookie boo-boo sugar bear.

07:35.888 --> 07:38.858
- Bleh!
What is happening to my family?

07:38.925 --> 07:40.259
- Knock, knock.

07:40.326 --> 07:42.728
- Who's there?
- This is not a joke, Lincoln.

07:42.795 --> 07:44.630
{\an1}Do you know
what's going on in the world?

07:44.697 --> 07:46.599
Here, take Mr. Coconuts.

07:46.666 --> 07:49.101
{\an1}He just reminds me
of all the trees being cut down

07:49.168 --> 07:50.903
in the rainforest.

07:50.970 --> 07:53.472
{\an3}- Wait, Luan--
what brought this on?

07:53.539 --> 07:55.775
- Well, ever since Luna left,

07:55.842 --> 07:57.643
{\an1}I've had no one
to try my jokes out on,

07:57.710 --> 08:00.112
so I've been watching
a lot of cable news.

08:00.179 --> 08:02.081
And what I've seen is horrific.

08:02.148 --> 08:04.183
So I've decided to become...

08:04.250 --> 08:05.718
an activist!

08:05.785 --> 08:07.320
- Don't be ridiculous.

08:07.386 --> 08:09.021
You're a comedian.

08:09.088 --> 08:10.389
[pie splatters]

08:10.456 --> 08:11.958
{\an3}See?
Funny, right?

08:12.024 --> 08:13.025
[rumbling]

08:13.092 --> 08:14.060
[animals howling]

08:14.126 --> 08:15.561
What the heck was that?

08:15.628 --> 08:17.697
{\an1}- They're just Lana's pets.
I liberated them.

08:17.763 --> 08:21.500
{\an1}And now I'm off to heal this
ticking time bomb we call Earth.

08:21.567 --> 08:23.102
{\an3}- Wait, Luan.
You can't be serious.

08:23.169 --> 08:24.103
[monkey screams]

08:24.170 --> 08:25.371
Argh!

08:25.438 --> 08:26.606
[monkey chattering]

08:26.672 --> 08:28.107
Get back here, Izzy!

08:28.174 --> 08:29.108
- [rattling]

08:29.175 --> 08:30.643
Izzy, come to Uncle Lincoln!

08:30.710 --> 08:33.511
<i>- And now for tonight's</i>
<i>top stories:</i>

08:33.578 --> 08:35.548
Former rising star
Luna Loud

08:35.615 --> 08:37.316
was kicked off
the Mick Swagger tour

08:37.383 --> 08:39.352
for destroying a hotel room.

08:39.418 --> 08:40.486
{\an8}- [in British accent]
All I wanted

08:40.553 --> 08:43.121
{\an8}was a bleeding pillow mint!

08:43.188 --> 08:44.590
- Luna?

08:44.657 --> 08:45.958
- In a "related" story,

08:46.025 --> 08:49.061
former comedian turned activist
Luan Loud

08:49.128 --> 08:51.631
has chained herself
to a giant redwood.

08:51.697 --> 08:53.266
- Hey, hey, ho, ho!

08:53.332 --> 08:55.134
Keep your hands off!
Let it grow!

08:55.201 --> 08:56.869
- Luan?

08:56.936 --> 08:58.604
- I'm being told
we have breaking news.

08:58.671 --> 09:01.107
- Please don't be
one of my sisters.

09:01.173 --> 09:03.409
{\an1}- Tucker, I'm here
at Flip's Food N' Fuel,

09:03.476 --> 09:05.044
{\an1}where two unknown bandits
have just made off

09:05.111 --> 09:07.680
with a carload of beef jerky
and a cotton candy machine.

09:07.747 --> 09:09.815
{\an3}- They're not unknown;
they're my sisters.

09:09.882 --> 09:11.250
{\an3}[slurping]

09:11.317 --> 09:13.552
{\an3}Their betrayal hurts more
than this brain freeze.

09:13.619 --> 09:15.021
{\an1}- I'm getting word
that the bandits

09:15.087 --> 09:17.590
{\an1}are currently leading police
on a slow-speed chase.

09:17.657 --> 09:19.625
[sirens wailing]

09:19.692 --> 09:21.761
[helicopters whirring]

09:21.827 --> 09:25.031
- Where did it all go wrong?

09:25.097 --> 09:26.399
- One has to wonder:

09:26.465 --> 09:28.100
where did it all go wrong
for these girls?

09:28.167 --> 09:31.103
And why is a four-year-old
working at a gas station?

09:31.170 --> 09:32.838
- Interview over!

09:32.905 --> 09:37.376
Wait--don't forget to come down
to Flip's Food N' Fuel,

09:37.443 --> 09:39.378
home of the Flippee!

09:39.445 --> 09:41.447
Now the interview's over.

09:42.415 --> 09:43.349
- I was watching that.

09:43.416 --> 09:44.717
{\an3}- Argh!

09:44.784 --> 09:47.887
{\an3}Lucy, at least you're
still normal.

09:47.954 --> 09:48.754
- [hissing]

09:48.821 --> 09:50.222
- Argh!
Not normal!

09:50.289 --> 09:52.925
- I was bitten by Lana's
liberated vampire bat.

09:52.992 --> 09:54.460
Greatest day ever.

09:54.527 --> 09:56.062
[smoke poofs]

09:56.128 --> 09:59.732
- Nine sisters lost, but
there's still one I can save.

09:59.799 --> 10:02.802
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:02.868 --> 10:04.270
Lily?

10:04.337 --> 10:05.304
[crashing]

10:05.371 --> 10:07.306
- [giggling]

10:07.373 --> 10:08.941
- Lily!

10:09.008 --> 10:11.110
Oh, no!
Lisa's chemicals!

10:11.177 --> 10:12.178
What have I done?

10:12.244 --> 10:15.348
- Mmm.
Yum, yum.

10:15.414 --> 10:17.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:17.917 --> 10:20.686
- Don't eat me, Lily!
[screaming]

10:20.753 --> 10:23.356
So that's the worst thing
that could happen.

10:23.422 --> 10:24.757
- [barking]

10:24.824 --> 10:27.660
- I totally agree.
I'm going to tell Lisa.

10:27.727 --> 10:29.528
- Tell Lisa what?
[gasping]

10:29.595 --> 10:32.365
- I was playing with my yo-yo,
and it got out of control

10:32.431 --> 10:34.767
and wrecked your experiment,
and I'm really, really sorry!

10:34.834 --> 10:36.936
Go ahead and disown me,
'cause I deserve it!

10:37.003 --> 10:39.405
{\an1}I'm confused.
You're not mad?

10:39.472 --> 10:41.507
{\an3}- Mad?
I'm ecstatic!

10:41.574 --> 10:43.509
You proved my hypothesis.

10:43.576 --> 10:45.778
{\an3}Your recklessness
was the one variable

10:45.845 --> 10:48.381
{\an3}my rigidly controlled experiment
sorely needed.

10:48.447 --> 10:49.982
- I'm still confused.

10:50.049 --> 10:52.551
{\an3}- I'm saying thank you
for being a clumsy doofus.

10:52.618 --> 10:54.720
{\an3}And thanks for admitting
what you did.

10:54.787 --> 10:56.088
- I didn't have a choice.

10:56.155 --> 10:57.656
{\an1}I didn't want you to work
at a gas station,

10:57.723 --> 10:59.725
{\an1}or Lynn and Lola to turn
to a life of crime,

10:59.792 --> 11:02.261
{\an1}or Lana to live in a bubble,
or--or--or--

11:02.328 --> 11:03.763
- Fascinating.

11:03.829 --> 11:06.465
{\an3}Exposure to my chemicals
seems to have damaged

11:06.532 --> 11:08.434
his cerebral cortex.

11:08.501 --> 11:09.869
- [sighs]

11:09.935 --> 11:11.437
Boy, am I glad
that nightmare's over.

11:11.504 --> 11:12.805
<i>[bell jingles]</i>

11:12.872 --> 11:16.275
<i>[joyful wedding music]</i>

11:16.342 --> 11:18.277
[screaming]

11:22.415 --> 11:25.551
{\an8}<i>[rock music]</i>

11:25.618 --> 11:30.056
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:30.122 --> 11:31.624
{\an8}[bell ringing]

11:31.690 --> 11:33.392
<i>- Okay, class,</i>
<i>we're at the halfway point</i>

11:33.459 --> 11:35.294
<i>of our energy</i>
<i>reduction project.</i>

11:35.361 --> 11:37.029
Let's see how you're doing.

11:37.096 --> 11:39.165
Great.
Very good.

11:39.231 --> 11:42.168
Ooh, very impressive, Clyde!

11:42.234 --> 11:43.536
- Thanks, Mrs. Johnson.

11:43.602 --> 11:45.671
{\an1}Our house is solar powered,
so we don't burn

11:45.738 --> 11:46.906
any fossil fuels.

11:46.972 --> 11:47.973
- Wonderful.

11:48.040 --> 11:49.575
You're all doing a great job

11:49.642 --> 11:51.811
{\an3}of reducing your eco-footprint
at home.

11:51.877 --> 11:53.312
And if you keep this up,

11:53.379 --> 11:56.649
{\an3}we'll definitely win
the Save a Polar Bear Challenge

11:56.715 --> 11:59.752
{\an9}and get this adorable little guy
named after us.

11:59.819 --> 12:02.121
{\an8}all: Aww...

12:02.188 --> 12:05.958
{\an9}- Oh, Lincoln, I see you haven't
made any progress.

12:06.025 --> 12:07.059
{\an8}What does this say?

12:07.126 --> 12:09.228
{\an8}"Have a heart,
do your part."

12:09.295 --> 12:11.697
{\an8}Do you not care
about polar bears?

12:11.764 --> 12:13.399
- [muffled voice]
No, I don't!

12:13.466 --> 12:14.834
I don't hate polar bears.
They're awesome!

12:14.900 --> 12:16.135
- What's that?
You hate polar bears?

12:16.202 --> 12:17.803
You're a polar bear hater?

12:17.870 --> 12:19.905
- [muffled voice]
No, I love them--they're cool.

12:19.972 --> 12:21.540
[all jeering]

12:21.607 --> 12:25.077
- If you make us lose, Lincoln,
you'll be an outcast!

12:25.144 --> 12:28.414
{\an3}- You might as well throw
your social life out the window.

12:28.481 --> 12:31.617
[all jeering]

12:33.385 --> 12:35.454
{\an1}- How am I supposed
to reduce our energy use?

12:35.521 --> 12:36.989
I've got ten sisters!

12:37.056 --> 12:39.158
{\an3}- I know, we'll just swoop in
from the left

12:39.225 --> 12:40.759
and annihilate them.

12:40.826 --> 12:42.995
{\an1}- What?
Annihilate my sisters?

12:43.062 --> 12:44.063
{\an3}- Huh? No.

12:44.130 --> 12:45.631
I was talking about our strategy

12:45.698 --> 12:48.067
for the "Swords and Cyborgs"
online tournament tomorrow.

12:48.134 --> 12:50.035
Preparation is key to victory.

12:50.102 --> 12:52.138
{\an1}- Oh, yeah.
Don't worry, I'll be ready.

12:52.204 --> 12:54.340
{\an1}But right now, I've got
bigger things to deal with.

12:54.406 --> 12:55.674
You heard our class:

12:55.741 --> 12:57.576
{\an1}if I don't get
my eco-meter in the green,

12:57.643 --> 12:59.145
I'll be a social outcast.

12:59.211 --> 13:00.446
- I'll still hang out with you--

13:00.513 --> 13:01.447
in secret, of course,

13:01.514 --> 13:02.848
{\an3}after dark.

13:02.915 --> 13:04.984
{\an3}Speaking of which,
the sun's going down.

13:05.050 --> 13:07.153
{\an3}I better get home
before the lights go out.

13:07.219 --> 13:09.989
[alarm blaring]

13:10.055 --> 13:12.925
- Maybe there's something wrong
with my eco-meter.

13:12.992 --> 13:15.528
[rumbling]

13:15.594 --> 13:16.896
Or not.
What can I do?

13:16.962 --> 13:18.764
In a family this big,

13:18.831 --> 13:22.301
our eco-footprint
is a size 18 triple wide.

13:22.368 --> 13:24.803
We use a lot of electricity...

13:24.870 --> 13:27.506
[stereo booming]

13:27.573 --> 13:30.776
- Bobby, you look so good
on all of my devices.

13:32.378 --> 13:34.613
[pie splatters, beeping]
- [laughing]

13:34.680 --> 13:36.582
<i>- Fossil fuels...</i>

13:42.821 --> 13:43.856
<i>Water...</i>

13:43.923 --> 13:45.057
- [humming]

13:48.594 --> 13:49.929
<i>- Aerosols...</i>

13:52.097 --> 13:53.799
<i>- Non-biodegradables...</i>

13:53.866 --> 13:56.602
<i>And did I mention electricity?</i>

13:58.804 --> 14:01.073
We've got to reduce
our eco-footprint.

14:01.140 --> 14:03.409
Hopefully I can get
my sisters on board.

14:03.475 --> 14:06.378
[all shouting at once]

14:06.445 --> 14:07.746
[pie splatters]

14:07.813 --> 14:11.383
- Or not.
Time to pull out the big guns.

14:11.450 --> 14:13.085
And if we don't all do our part,

14:13.152 --> 14:16.121
this adorable little guy
won't survive.

14:16.188 --> 14:18.958
[all crying]

14:19.024 --> 14:20.526
- But what can we do?

14:20.593 --> 14:22.428
- I'm glad you asked.

14:22.494 --> 14:23.796
{\an3}You don't need
all these devices.

14:23.862 --> 14:25.231
- Yes, I do.

14:25.297 --> 14:27.967
{\an1}Bobby and I like to admire
each other from multiple angles.

14:28.033 --> 14:31.036
<i>- Hey, Lincoln.</i>
<i>"Hola" from France.</i>

14:31.103 --> 14:34.173
- Who is that girl,
and why is she smiling at you?

14:34.240 --> 14:35.574
<i>- Babe, that's the "Mona Lisa."</i>

14:35.641 --> 14:38.010
{\an3}- Instead of using
all of these,

14:38.077 --> 14:40.279
{\an3}why don't you write
Bobby a letter?

14:40.346 --> 14:42.114
- Why don't I rip your little--

14:42.181 --> 14:43.882
- Polar bear.
- Aww...

14:43.949 --> 14:45.985
Okay, I'll write him a letter.

14:46.051 --> 14:49.054
And maybe I'll send one to
that little flirt Mona too.

14:49.121 --> 14:50.422
[water splashes]

14:50.489 --> 14:53.058
{\an3}- But how will I keep
my reptiles warm?

14:53.125 --> 14:55.194
{\an3}They're cold-blooded,
you know.

14:55.261 --> 14:56.562
- But you're not.

15:01.500 --> 15:03.002
- [laughing]

15:03.068 --> 15:05.704
- Instead of powering your lab
with megawatts of electricity,

15:05.771 --> 15:09.541
{\an1}why not use
a renewable resource?

15:09.608 --> 15:12.511
{\an1}- [gasps]
Lincoln, this is genius.

15:12.578 --> 15:14.079
- Fresh energy coming at you.

15:14.146 --> 15:17.683
This one's got to be good
for at least 75 watts.

15:17.750 --> 15:19.084
[electricity buzzing]

15:20.319 --> 15:21.654
- [screaming]

15:21.720 --> 15:23.689
{\an1}- Leni, instead of taking
multiple showers a day,

15:23.756 --> 15:26.225
{\an1}how about using this refreshing
moist towelette?

15:26.292 --> 15:29.561
{\an3}- And clog my pores?
No way!

15:29.628 --> 15:33.866
{\an3}Aww...
okay.

15:33.932 --> 15:36.235
{\an3}Do you mind?
I'm showering.

15:37.803 --> 15:39.471
{\an3}- Luan, instead of wasting
all that energy

15:39.538 --> 15:41.106
making more pies,

15:41.173 --> 15:44.343
{\an3}why not get some comedy out
of your leftover banana peels?

15:44.410 --> 15:47.279
{\an1}- That old gag?
I don't think so.

15:47.346 --> 15:48.647
{\an3}- Whoa!

15:48.714 --> 15:52.284
{\an3}- Actually, I'm starting
to see the a-peel!

15:52.351 --> 15:53.886
{\an3}[laughing]

15:53.952 --> 15:55.287
[alarm blaring]

15:55.354 --> 15:56.522
[watch dings]

15:56.588 --> 15:58.190
- We're getting there.

15:58.257 --> 16:01.193
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

16:01.260 --> 16:04.196
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:04.263 --> 16:07.299
[electric guitar strumming]

16:07.366 --> 16:08.967
- [whistling]

16:09.034 --> 16:16.975
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:21.747 --> 16:23.082
Almost there.

16:25.351 --> 16:26.618
[ding]

16:26.685 --> 16:28.153
We did it!

16:28.220 --> 16:30.089
[all cheering]

16:30.155 --> 16:32.658
- See what we can accomplish
when we all do our part?

16:32.725 --> 16:34.293
All we have to do
is keep the house in the green

16:34.360 --> 16:35.594
till the end of the week,

16:35.661 --> 16:37.596
and that polar bear
will be safe--

16:37.663 --> 16:39.832
and so will my social life.

16:39.898 --> 16:41.867
- Say it proud.
We're green and Loud!

16:41.934 --> 16:44.103
{\an3}all: Say it proud--
we're green and Loud!

16:44.169 --> 16:46.372
{\an3}Say it proud--
we're green and Loud!

16:46.438 --> 16:48.340
{\an1}<i>- Lincoln!</i>
<i>Come in, Lincoln!</i>

16:48.407 --> 16:50.943
- Clyde, I'm not supposed to be
talking on this right now.

16:51.009 --> 16:52.778
We're reducing
our eco-footprint.

16:52.845 --> 16:54.179
<i>- But it's tournament time.</i>

16:54.246 --> 16:55.914
<i>"Swords and Cyborgs"!</i>

16:55.981 --> 16:58.117
- Oh, right.
Just let me go get my laptop.

16:58.183 --> 17:00.152
{\an3}<i>all: Yes, we care!</i>
<i>We'll save that bear!</i>

17:00.219 --> 17:02.788
- What am I saying?
I can't use my laptop.

17:02.855 --> 17:04.423
We've finally gone green
in the house,

17:04.490 --> 17:05.824
and I can't mess it up.

17:05.891 --> 17:07.893
<i>- Well, there's always</i>
<i>next year.</i>

17:07.960 --> 17:09.795
- No, no, no.
I'll make it work.

17:09.862 --> 17:12.698
One laptop won't make
that big of a difference.

17:15.968 --> 17:19.104
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:19.171 --> 17:23.675
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:23.742 --> 17:25.042
[alarm blaring]
Whoops!

17:25.109 --> 17:26.979
I got to get us
back in the green.

17:29.515 --> 17:30.849
- Hey, what the--

17:30.916 --> 17:33.652
- Remember this guy?
- Yes, we saved him.

17:33.719 --> 17:35.220
- Well, he's got siblings too.

17:35.287 --> 17:37.923
Do you hate siblings?
Are you sibling haters?

17:37.990 --> 17:39.792
- Well, I'm starting to.

17:42.895 --> 17:46.131
- Hey, guys,
our neighborhood's on TV!

17:47.566 --> 17:48.934
- Hey, Lincoln.
- Argh!

17:49.001 --> 17:50.536
{\an1}Clyde, what are you
doing here?

17:50.602 --> 17:52.004
- The sun went behind a cloud.

17:52.070 --> 17:53.705
My solar house lost power.

17:53.772 --> 17:55.374
Is it okay if I play here?

17:55.441 --> 17:56.875
[alarm blaring]

17:56.942 --> 17:58.977
{\an1}- I just got us back
into the green.

17:59.044 --> 18:01.880
{\an3}- Sorry, Lincoln, I didn't mean
to cause a problem.

18:01.947 --> 18:03.949
{\an3}- No, no, Clyde.
Not a problem.

18:04.016 --> 18:06.318
I'll just go make an adjustment.

18:06.385 --> 18:07.586
[knocking]

18:07.653 --> 18:08.987
If it's yellow, let it mellow!

18:09.054 --> 18:11.223
<i>- Um, what if it's not?</i>

18:11.290 --> 18:14.259
- If it's brown,
keep it around.

18:14.326 --> 18:15.294
{\an1}<i>- Ew!</i>

18:15.360 --> 18:17.296
{\an1}<i>Aww...</i>

18:17.362 --> 18:20.833
- Hey, guys, think we could
turn off the AC?

18:20.899 --> 18:22.634
- But we're trying to stay cool.

18:22.701 --> 18:24.536
- You know who else
wants to stay cool?

18:24.603 --> 18:25.671
This guy.

18:25.737 --> 18:28.140
{\an1}- Aww...

18:28.207 --> 18:30.676
[AC crashing]

18:30.742 --> 18:33.946
- Look, I'm your number one fan!
[laughing]

18:34.012 --> 18:36.114
{\an1}- [laughing]
Good one, honey.

18:36.181 --> 18:37.749
Well, I'm off.

18:37.816 --> 18:39.952
{\an3}- Hey, Dad, instead of taking
the car,

18:40.018 --> 18:41.954
{\an3}why not enjoy
a little fresh air?

18:42.020 --> 18:43.689
{\an1}- I'm picking up your mom
from the airport.

18:43.755 --> 18:46.325
- Then you'll need this.

18:46.391 --> 18:48.527
[alarm dinging]

18:48.594 --> 18:49.995
What are you guys doing here?

18:50.062 --> 18:51.964
- Can't play "Sword and Cyborgs"
at our houses.

18:52.030 --> 18:53.465
We're in the green zone.

18:53.532 --> 18:54.700
- Well, so am I--

18:54.766 --> 18:56.602
or I was.

18:56.668 --> 18:58.670
{\an1}- Well, if it's a problem,
we can go.

18:58.737 --> 19:01.607
- No, no, no.
I'll make an adjustment.

19:01.673 --> 19:04.676
[grunting]

19:08.480 --> 19:09.515
- Ahh.

19:09.581 --> 19:12.351
[crashing, groaning]

19:12.417 --> 19:13.752
{\an1}- Sweet!
Snacks!

19:13.819 --> 19:15.454
{\an1}Let's put them by
the air conditioner

19:15.521 --> 19:16.822
we found outside.

19:16.889 --> 19:18.423
[alarm blaring]

19:18.490 --> 19:22.160
{\an1}But if it's not cool, Lincoln,
I mean, just say the word.

19:22.227 --> 19:24.463
- No, no.
Adjustment.

19:24.530 --> 19:27.466
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

19:27.533 --> 19:35.140
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:35.207 --> 19:37.543
Can't run the washer
if there's nothing to wash.

19:37.609 --> 19:46.318
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:46.385 --> 19:50.289
What else is there?

19:50.355 --> 19:51.723
[dinging]

19:51.790 --> 19:54.459
- We are in the green.
Let's do this!

19:54.526 --> 19:58.430
- Whew, what stinks?

19:58.497 --> 20:00.098
- Game over, Lincoln!

20:00.165 --> 20:02.167
- It's not what it looks like!

20:02.234 --> 20:04.036
{\an3}- We're up there making
all these sacrifices,

20:04.102 --> 20:06.271
{\an3}and you're down here playing
some stupid computer game?

20:06.338 --> 20:09.207
- Okay, so maybe it is
what it looks like.

20:09.274 --> 20:12.444
- If you don't want to
give anything up, why should we?

20:12.511 --> 20:14.713
{\an8}- But--but--
polar bear?

20:14.780 --> 20:16.381
- Aww--wait a minute.

20:16.448 --> 20:18.150
You can't use that
on us anymore.

20:18.216 --> 20:21.587
- Come on, girls.
Let's go get our stuff back.

20:21.653 --> 20:25.357
- And a refill.

20:25.424 --> 20:27.726
{\an1}- Well, I guess you're
going back into the red.

20:27.793 --> 20:30.295
{\an3}- Which means you're gonna lose
the polar bear challenge

20:30.362 --> 20:31.530
for our class.

20:31.597 --> 20:33.532
{\an1}- Which means we can't
be seen with you.

20:33.599 --> 20:37.235
{\an3}- Which means your social life
is out the window.

20:37.302 --> 20:39.371
- Guys, wait!
Come back!

20:39.438 --> 20:40.906
I can make adjustments.

20:40.973 --> 20:43.609
I blew it.
- Don't worry, Lincoln.

20:43.675 --> 20:46.778
{\an1}I'll still hang out with you--
in secret, of course.

20:46.845 --> 20:48.313
{\an3}- It's not about that,
Clyde.

20:48.380 --> 20:50.282
{\an3}I don't care
if the class hates me.

20:50.349 --> 20:52.384
{\an3}What I should have cared about
all along is--

20:52.451 --> 20:53.385
{\an3}this guy.

20:53.452 --> 20:54.653
{\an7}- Aww...

20:54.720 --> 20:57.089
{\an3}- Exactly.
Our class has done their part.

20:57.155 --> 20:58.890
My sisters have done theirs.

20:58.957 --> 21:00.993
{\an3}Now it's time for me
to do mine.

21:02.828 --> 21:05.764
[stereo blasting rock music]

21:05.831 --> 21:06.965
♪ ♪

21:07.032 --> 21:10.469
[pie splatters, beeping]
- [laughing]

21:10.535 --> 21:12.504
- [humming]

21:12.571 --> 21:13.672
[electricity buzzing]

21:13.739 --> 21:16.274
- [laughing]

21:16.341 --> 21:18.377
- [giggling]
Oh, Bobby.

21:18.443 --> 21:20.679
You got me a present?
I can't wait to see it.

21:20.746 --> 21:25.550
- [panting]

21:25.617 --> 21:27.486
<i>- Lincoln, pedal faster!</i>

21:27.552 --> 21:31.023
{\an3}<i>I'm downloading a pic</i>
<i>from Bobby.</i>

21:31.089 --> 21:32.958
- Amazing work, class.

21:33.025 --> 21:35.427
We won the polar bear challenge!

21:35.494 --> 21:38.563
And I took the liberty
of naming him...

21:38.630 --> 21:40.832
Mrs. Johnson!

21:40.899 --> 21:42.501
all: Mrs. Johnson?
[muttering]

21:42.567 --> 21:45.237
- Let's all give Lincoln
a round of applause

21:45.303 --> 21:49.041
for stepping up his green game
and doing his part.

21:49.107 --> 21:51.109
[all cheering]

21:51.176 --> 21:54.713
- Well, I saved the polar bear,
and I'm not an outcast.

21:54.780 --> 21:57.149
Although,
technically speaking,

21:57.215 --> 22:02.054
my social life
is out the window.

22:02.120 --> 22:04.589
Do you mind?
I'm showering!

22:10.529 --> 22:11.963
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:12.030 --> 22:13.832
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:13.899 --> 22:16.768
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.835 --> 22:19.237
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:19.304 --> 22:23.308
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:23.375 --> 22:24.676
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:24.743 --> 22:26.078
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:26.144 --> 22:27.446
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:27.512 --> 22:28.680
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:28.747 --> 22:30.115
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:30.182 --> 22:32.651
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.718 --> 22:35.253
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:35.320 --> 22:36.588
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
